msgid "The AP Calculus course doesn't require knowing the proofs of these rules, but we believe that as long as a proof is accessible, there's always something to learn from it. In general, it's always good to require some kind of proof or justification for the theorems you learn."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/math/old-ap-calc-bc/bc-differentiation-1-new/bc-3-6/a/justifying-the-basic-derivative-rules">http://translate.khanacademy.org/math/old-ap-calc-bc/bc-differentiation-1-new/bc-3-6/a/justifying-the-basic-derivative-rules</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "The basic derivative rules tell us how to find the derivatives of constant functions, functions multiplied by constants, and of sums/differences of functions."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/math/old-ap-calc-bc/bc-differentiation-1-new/bc-3-6/a/justifying-the-basic-derivative-rules">http://translate.khanacademy.org/math/old-ap-calc-bc/bc-differentiation-1-new/bc-3-6/a/justifying-the-basic-derivative-rules</a>.
# (KA_SOURCE_TREE: shared)
# (format: perseus_text)
#: intl/datastore:1
msgid ""
"||\n"
":- | :-\n"
"**Constant rule** | $\\dfrac{d}{dx}k=0$\n"
"**Constant multiple rule** | $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[k\\cdot f(x)]=k\\cdot\\dfrac{d}{dx}f(x)$\n"
"**Sum rule** | $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[f(x)+g(x)]=\\dfrac{d}{dx}f(x)+\\dfrac{d}{dx}g(x)$\n"
"**Difference rule** | $\\dfrac{d}{dx}[f(x)-g(x)]=\\dfrac{d}{dx}f(x)-\\dfrac{d}{dx}g(x)$"
msgstr ""
